content_vision: My silent mood. It happened. I need my space. Depression, traumas are fucking me up. Trust issues, past demons are haunting me. I feel lost.
text:
Intro:
My silent mood may seem aloof, but it's just a shield against the pain,
I won't let my past demons win, I won't bow down to their game.

Verse 1:
Trying to find my way out of this maze, but my mind keeps playing cruel games,
searching for salvation in a daze, but my past won't let me disengage.
My mind is a battlefield, fighting with every memory, every scar, but I won't let them defeat me,
I'll keep marching on, one step at a time.
Trying to rise above the ashes, but my demons pull me back down, it's a constant battle for my sanity,
my smile just a mask to hide my frown.
But in your arms, I find solace and peace,
my heart finally at ease as my worries decrease.

Pre-Chorus 1:
Every day, I try to push away, the memories that still cause me pain,
But you come along, just one look, and suddenly they all fade away.

Chorus 1:
But I won't let my past define me,
I'll rise above and keep shining bright
Even when I'm feeling lost and alone,
your love guides me back home.

Verse 2:
I try to find my footing, but my past won't let me stand, it's like quicksand pulling me under,
into a world I can't understand.
But in your arms, I find solace and peace,
my heart finally at ease as my worries decrease.
But your love, like a lighthouse in the storm, guides me back to shore,
where I am finally safe from harm.
But I still can't shake off these chains, they hold me tight and I'm suffocating,
but with you by my side, I can finally breathe again.

Pre-Chorus 2:
But you, my love, you've seen me at my worst, and still, you chose to stay,
despite my flaws and my mistakes, you love me anyway.

Chorus 2:
But when I'm with you, all the pieces fall into place,
and I know I've found my safe haven in your embrace.
Lost and alone, but in your arms,
I'm finally home

Bridge:
But with you by my side, I find the courage to face my fears,
and together we conquer the doubts and tears.
But with your love, I have found my way out of the darkness, each step guided by your hand,
and with your unwavering support, I know I can withstand.
